&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Royal Brompton Hospital/Harefield Hospital&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Private Patients &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bank Education &amp; Training Officer  &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 5 &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ref:312-PP-BANK-0954&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full-time&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bank &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you confident in digital content creation and management with strong administration skills?  We have recently established a new microsite dedicated to our educational activities and require someone to comfortably manage the day to day management of the website and development of new content. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Royal Brompton &amp; Harefield NHS Foundation Trust is the largest heart and lung centre in the UK and among the largest in Europe. We are a partnership of two specialist hospitals which are known throughout the world for our expertise, standard of care and research success. We have recently been recognised as one of the world’s best hospitals by Newsweek in the specialised category of heart and lung care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to join our dynamic team and be a part of our new education and training initiative.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PURPOSE &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic individual who will a prime team member in the expansion and organisation of our education and training activities, such as webinars, courses, events and fellowships. Additionally, you will be expected to actively look out for viable opportunities to advance and grow all our offerings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Duties:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage content development for education microsite including copywriting and basic design elements (some WordPress experience would be useful)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead on contacting consultants and other members of the organisation in order to source new and existing educational content&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expand and support our webinar course offerings for both primary care and international market&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please read the personal specification and job description for full details of responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;.    &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Should you require any further information regarding this post please contact &lt;strong&gt;Ruku Bibi&lt;/strong&gt; via email on &lt;strong&gt;r.bibi@rbht.nhs.uk &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing Date:&lt;/strong&gt;         20 Novemeber 2020&lt;/p&gt;
